{"_id":"NDQzMGNkYzdmOWEz","name":"Robe of Eyes","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"ZDVkNGI3NGVkMTk0","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":63,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":630000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<p></p><h4>Robe of Eyes</h4><i>Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)</i><p></p><p>This robe is adorned with eyelike patterns. While you wear the robe, you gain the following benefits:<br><br>• The robe lets you see in all directions, and you have advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on sight.<br><br>• You have darkvision out to a range of 120 feet.<br><br>• You can see invisible creatures and objects, as well as see into the Ethereal Plane, out to a range of 120 feet.<br><br>The eyes on the robe can't be closed or averted. Although you can close or avert your own eyes, you are never considered to be doing so while wearing this robe.<br><br>A<a href=\"https://roll20.net/compendium/dnd5e/Spells:Light/#h-Light\"> </a><i><a href=\"https://roll20.net/compendium/dnd5e/Spells:Light/#h-Light\">light</a></i><a href=\"https://roll20.net/compendium/dnd5e/Spells:Light/#h-Light\"> </a>spell cast on the robe or a <i><a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=Item data-id=ZTlkM2Y3YzkyNTIw ><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i>daylight</a> </i>spell cast within 5 feet of the robe causes you to be blinded for 1 minute. At the end of each of your turns, you can make a Constitution saving throw (DC 11 for <i>light </i>or DC 15 for <i>daylight</i>), ending the blindness on a success.<br></p>","img":"assets/art/shared_worlds/journal/029_-_Magic_Items/063_-_Robe_of_Eyes/avatar_1.png"}
{"_id":"NDQzOWVlZmY1ZGVi","name":"Underground Forest","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"MDU0YWU4MzFmMTE1","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":1,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":10000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h1>Underground Forest</h1><p>The River of the Depths connects the fourth and fifth levels of Undermountain, skirting the edges of vast caverns filled with trees, shrubs, birds, other animals, and sunlight. An entire forest, as real as any found on the surface, waits to be explored, but an archdruid protects it. And explorers traveling downriver have seen a huge green dragon as well, perched on a tower near a bridge that spans the river.</p><div><br></div>","img":"assets/art/shared_worlds/journal/032_-_Secrets_Deck_Handouts/001_-_Underground_Forest/avatar.png"}
