{"_id":"YWQ1OGZiOTgxZWQ1","name":"Midnight Tears","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"ZTAwZjhmZTU5ZGU5","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":9,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":90000,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p><b><i>Midnight Tears (Ingested).</i></b> A creature that ingests this poison suffers no effect until the stroke of midnight. If the poison has not been neutralized before then, the creature must succeed on a DC 17 Constitution saving throw, taking 31 (9d6) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p></section>","img":""}
{"_id":"YWU0YzkwMzY3MDBk","name":"Candle of Invocation","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"ZDVkNGI3NGVkMTk0","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":10,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":100000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h4>Candle of Invocation</h4><p><i>Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunement)</i><br></p><p>The candle's magic is activated when the candle is lit, which requires an action. After burning for 4 hours, the candle is destroyed. You can snuff it out early for use at a later time. Deduct the time it burned in increments of 1 minute from the candle's total burn time.<br><br>While lit, the candle sheds dim light in a 30-foot radius. Any creature within that light whose alignment matches that of the candle makes attack rolls, saving throws, and ability checks with advantage. In addition, a cleric or druid in the light whose alignment matches the candle's can cast 1st-level spells he or she has prepared without expending spell slots, though the spell's effect is as if cast with a 1st-level slot.<br><br>Alternatively, when you light the candle for the first time, you can cast the <i><a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=Item data-id=ODY3NjQxZWRhNTM1 ><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i>gate</a></i> spell with it. Doing so destroys the candle.<br></p>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p><br></p></section>","img":"assets/art/shared_worlds/journal/029_-_Magic_Items/010_-_Candle_of_Invocation/avatar_1.png"}
